CSS:

Css or Cascading Style sheets, is used to style and format web pages created with HTML.

CSS

we use css to style an HTML document. 
CSS describes how HTML elements be displayed. 

<h1 style="color:red">VIjay<h1>

3 ways 

1. Inline CSS
2. Internal CSS
3. External CSS

1. Inline CSS

<html>

<head>
	<title>HTML WEB ELEMENT</title>
	<p style="background-color:red">Apple<p>
	<p style="background-color:orange">Orange<p>
	<p style="background-color:yellow">Mango<p>
		
</head>
<body>
</body>
</html>


